  "bookId": 21,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A girl in foreign attire, skilled in an unusual martial art.\nShe possesses a strange constitution that allows her to regenerate her body by eating.",
  "personality": "Usually appears to be spacing out, but she does listen to what others say - she's just slow to react. Sometimes she says surprisingly wise things.",
  "like": "Drumsticks, prayer beads",
  "familiarData": "A human girl who lost her memories and woke up in the wilderness wearing foreign attire. She can deliver strikes powerful enough to pierce rock using an unusual martial arts stance.\nAmnesia didn't hinder Lunchun's daily life. She neither cares about her past nor has any plans for the future. Most of the time, Lunchun only cares about how to get her next meal.\nWith her vacant stare, aversion to sunlight, and unusual body movements, those around her feel she doesn't seem quite human. To these questions, she always smiles and answers: \"I'm a zombie, you know.\"\nEven without a weapon she can fight back, and wounds heal rapidly through eating. This made slave hunters who tried to capture her fail repeatedly, and she ended up wandering the wilderness long-term.\nLunchun is actually quite good at cooking, but due to her constitution she can't get near fire, which gives her quite a headache. She met Kara in the wilderness; both love to eat meat in big bites, so they became good friends.",
  "familiarUnlockLevel": 5,
